The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Municipal poll meet
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Municipal poll meet
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, March 5: The state election commission has called a meeting on March 10 to take the views of the main political parties regarding the coming elections to 82 civic bodies.        
	Of the 82 municipalities that would go to polls around May-June, the Congress independently runs 13, Trinamul 3 and the Congress-Trinamul combine 5. The Left controls 61 civic boards.        
	Leaders from the Left, Trinamul Congress, Congress, BJP and other parties are likely to attend the meet.        
	A state election official said that the elections would be held in 1801 wards spread across the 82 municipalities.                                                                                                                                                             
